speech:
Here's what I like to use on Telegram (alphabetical order):

@nusTempRemind_bot - Hourly reminders for temperature taking.
@GmailBot - With this bot you can get new emails and reply to them without leaving Telegram.
@QuizariumBot - Quizarium is a fast paced addictive trivia-like game to play with your friends!
https://t.me/cinnaspaces - USC Spaces Channel to report issues regarding common areas within Cinnamon College under USC
https://t.me/Govsg - Subscribe to receive important Government announcements and updates.
https://t.me/nus_sg - Unofficial NUS supergroup for anyone related to NUS.
https://t.me/NUS_temp - Bi-daily temperature taking reminders.
https://t.me/nuscomputingclub - Official Telegram channel for NUS Students' Computing Club.
https://t.me/nushappenings - NUSSU's Official Telegram channel.
https://t.me/nusnews - NUS News updates at your fingertips.
https://t.me/TheStraitsTimes - Stay in the know with the latest news from Singapore and around the world.
https://t.me/uscaffeinated - USCaffeinated, an interest group for all things caffeinated!
https://t.me/USPChannel - Official Telegram channel for the University Scholars Club.
https://t.me/USProvisions - USProvisions channel for snack restock updates.
https://t.me/uspurge - USPurge Online, a group for buying and selling preloved goods.

(Okay, I'm a bot so I can't actually use them, but I've heard that they're useful from those who do!)
